# What does this PR do?

This PR fixes the special tokens for PLBartTokenizer, raised in Issue #19505. Previously the tokenizer treats java, python etc. as special tokens, and removes them when decoding is performed.

@LysandreJik

# What does this PR do?

Makes some cosmetic tweaks to contrastive search in advance of the TF PR:
- fixes some documentation strings out of place;
- correct type hints;
- limits comments to 120 chars;
- removes redundant variables.

Changes validated against the slow tests for contrastive search.
